    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl>Morelli in <ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>270</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>105510</citedRange></bibl>.</p>    
              </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <div type="textpart" subtype="side" n="a"><ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Νικόβωλος">Νικό<supplied reason="lost">βωλος</supplied></name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Καρνεάδας" type="patronymic">Καρνε<supplied reason="lost">άδα</supplied></name></persName></persName>
                </ab></div>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="side" n="b"><ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Νικόβωλος">Νικόβ<supplied reason="lost">ωλος</supplied></name></persName> 
                </ab></div>
                      </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="a.1">
                        <lem>Νικό<supplied reason="lost">βωλος</supplied></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir">Νικό<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></rdg>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="a.2">
                        <lem>Καρνε<supplied reason="lost">άδα</supplied></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir">Καρν<unclear>ε</unclear><supplied reason="lost">άδου</supplied> <note>this ending is also possible</note></rdg>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="b.1">
                        <lem>Νικόβ<supplied reason="lost">ωλος</supplied></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig><unclear>ι</unclear>νικθρ</orig></rdg></app>
                </p>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>a) Nikobôlos fils de Karnéadès.</p>
            <p>b) Nikobôlos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>a) Nikobolos son of Karneades.</p>
            <p>b) Nikobolos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>a) Nikobolos figlio di Karneades.</p>
             <p>b) Nikobolos.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>It is difficult to decide whether the inscription on the upper face was inscribed earlier than the one on the front face, which is more
                monumental and also better preserved. However there should have been, if ever, a very short span of time between them.</p>
                <p>The layout of b) makes plausible that only name and father's name stood on the front face. If so, there was no room on the upper face
                for the father's name to be mentioned.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
